Definition.WordDefinition: Interact \In`ter*act"\, n. [Pref. inter- + act. Cf. {Entr'acte}.] A short act or piece between others, as in a play; an interlude; hence, intermediate employment or time. --Chesterfield. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Interact \In`ter*act"\, v. i. To act upon each other; as, two agents mutually interact. --Emerson. --Tyndall. [1913 Webster]
interact v : act together or towards others or with others; "He should interact more with his colleagues"
